User Manual – Netflix ETL Pipeline

This guide explains how to download the project from GitHub and run it on your local system.


1. Prerequisites

Make sure you have these installed:
   -Python 3.8+ (https://www.python.org/downloads/)
   -Apache Spark (https://spark.apache.org/downloads.html)
   -PostgreSQL (https://www.postgresql.org/download/)
   -Git (to download the project)


2. Clone the Repository

Open terminal (or Command Prompt) and run:

    git clone https://github.com/yourusername/netflix  etl.git
    cd netflix  etl


3. Install Dependencies

Inside the project folder, install required Python libraries:

    pip install   r requirements.txt

                                                                                                               
4. Setup PostgreSQL
                                                                                                                        
1. Start PostgreSQL server.
2. Create a database (default is 'postgres').
3. Update load.py with your PostgreSQL credentials if needed:

    dbname="postgres"
    user="postgres"
    password="postgres"
    host="localhost"
    port="5432"

                                                                                                                        
5. Run ETL Pipeline
                                                                                                                        
Run each step in order:

Step 1 – Extract
    python extract.py /path/to/extract

Step 2 – Transform
    python transform.py /path/to/extract /path/to/output

Step 3 – Load
    python load.py /path/to/output

                                                                                                                        
6. Verify Data
                                                                                                                        
Open PostgreSQL and check if the table is created:

    SELECT * FROM netflix_shows LIMIT 10;

                                                                                                                        
7. Create Visualizations (Optional)
                                                                                                                        
1. Install Apache Superset (https://superset.apache.org/).
2. Connect Superset to your PostgreSQL database.
3. Explore tables → Create bar charts, pie charts, etc.

                                                                                                                        
Done! 
You now have the Netflix dataset cleaned, transformed, and loaded into PostgreSQL, ready for visualization.
